    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 7 Engine Service Manual - Cylinder Head and Valve Train - Installation
        - Roller Hydraulic Cam Followers
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s10.4.5" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Roller Hydraulic Cam Followers</title>
        <figure id="f3450010072" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM08/M08140.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Roller hydraulic cam followers (typical)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Roller hydraulic cam follower (4)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Roller follower guide</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, keep cam followers and push rods in the order removed and install in
                    original order.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Place rollers hydraulic cam followers in roller follower guides with the lubrication holes
                    oriented as noted during removal.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate and place each roller hydraulic cam follower in its respective roller follower
                guide.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450010073" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM08/M08139.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Cam follower and guide assemblies (typical)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Lifter guide bolt with washer assembly (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Cam follower and guide assembly (2)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate roller hydraulic cam followers with clean engine oil and install cam followers and
                guide assemblies in correct location.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install two lifter guide bolt with washer assemblies. Tighten bolts to
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_236.xml" xrefid="s10.t2">special torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s10.t2"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
